    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-07T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-07T18:00:00-05:00" n="227"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d227">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.3362i/16: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-07T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 7, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>102. Embassy’s telegram No. 163, July 28, 1 p.m. With regard to the suggestion
                    made relative to the <hi rend="italic">Alden</hi>, the Department assumes that
                    there is no prospect that the Japanese authorities will take favorable action.
                    In reply to a communication from the Japanese Embassy here,<note n="47"
                        xml:id="d227fn1">Not printed.</note> the Department is today returning an
                    adverse answer<note n="47" xml:id="d227fn2">Not printed.</note> to that
                    Embassy’s request that the Japanese Government training ship <hi rend="italic"
                        >Shintoku Maru</hi> be permitted to enter a Hawaiian harbor which is not
                    listed as a port of entry.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
